typeof      ~   Tells you the type of any value as a string.
typeof "hi"        // "string"
typeof 123         // "number"
typeof true        // "boolean"
typeof []          // "object" ðŸ˜• (yes, arrays are objects)
typeof null        // "object" (quirk of JS)

isNaN()     ~   Checks if a value is NaN (Not a Number).
isNaN("hi")        // true (because "hi" can't be converted to a number)
isNaN(123)         // false
isNaN("123")       // false (it's a valid number string)

Array.isArray   ~   Specifically checks if something is an array.
Array.isArray([1, 2, 3])     // true
Array.isArray("hello")       // false
Array.isArray({})            // false
